The paper proposes a method for automatically designing scoring functions for knowledge graph embedding, which involves machine learning techniques and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with natural language processing. Additionally, the paper involves working with databases (knowledge graphs), which suggests the sub-category cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper deals with link prediction and triplets classification, which are tasks related to information retrieval, suggesting the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
